/*
The function readInt16x10 converts a 16-bit signed integer value to a floating-point value divided by 10. 
It handles negative values by subtracting 65536 from them. 
However, there is a unique case when the value -1 is encoded as -0.1 in Int16x10 format.

To handle this case, we explicitly check if the input value is -1. 
If it is, we return -0.1 instead of the default behavior of returning 65535. 
This ensures that the correct value is returned when -1 is encoded as -0.1.

Example usage:
const value = -1;
const result = readInt16x10(value); // Returns -0.1
*/

function readInt16x10(value) {
    if (value === 65535) {
        return -0.1;
    }

    if (value > 32767) {
        value = value - 65536;
    }

    return value / 10.0;
}

